      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\docs\\\\sops\\\\CHROME-DEVTOOLS-AI-MECHANISM.md\", \"offset\": 420, \"limit\": 80}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\sops\\CHROME-DEVTOOLS-AI-MECHANISM.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ## The .ailog Schema (Original)\n424: \n425: Chrome DevTools AI originally used the `.ailog` schema:\n426: \n427: ```json\n428: {\n429:   \"user-query\": \"Why is this element not visible?\",\n430:   \"title\": \"Debugging visibility issue\",\n431:   \"thought\": \"The element might have display:none or visibility:hidden\",\n432:   \"action\": {\n433:     \"code\": \"getComputedStyle(element).display\",\n434:     \"output\": \"none\"\n435:   },\n436:   \"answer\": \"The element has display: none set in the CSS\",\n437:   \"side-effect\": {\n438:     \"action\": \"file_write\",\n439:     \"path\": \"styles.css\"\n440:   },\n441:   \"context\": {\n442:     \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n443:     \"element\": \"div#main\"\n444:   }\n445: }\n446: ```\n447: \n448: This evolved into the AgentSON schema.\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## Key Differences from Other Tools\n453: \n454: | Feature | Chrome DevTools AI | opencode | MiniMax |\n455: |---------|-------------------|----------|---------|\n456: | **Storage** | **Unknown** | SQLite | SQLite |\n457: | **Format** | **Unknown** | Relational tables | Relational tables |\n458: | **Export** | Copy to agent | Custom script | Custom script |\n459: | **Schema** | **Unknown** | Custom | Custom |\n460: | **Context** | Page elements, network, performance | Code, files | Code, files |\n461: | **Reader Status** | **Not implemented** | Working | Working |\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: ## Why This Matters\n466: \n467: ### 1. Portability\n468: \n469: ```\n470: Chrome DevTools AI → AgentSON → Any coding agent\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ### 2. Searchability\n474: \n475: ```bash\n476: # Search across all Chrome DevTools AI sessions\n477: grep -r \"performance\" *.AgentSON\n478: ```\n479: \n480: ### 3. Hydration\n481: \n482: ```\n483: Debug in Chrome → Export to AgentSON → Continue in Cursor\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ### 4. Evidence\n487: \n488: ```\n489: Full trace of debugging session for:\n490: - Code reviews\n491: - Bug reports\n492: - Documentation\n493: - Learning\n494: ```\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ## Why This Matters\n499: \n\n(Showing lines 420-499 of 606. Use offset=500 to continue.)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783217811045
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\PRD.md\", \"offset\": 105, \"limit\": 30}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\PRD.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n105:   \"side-effect\": \"Updated styles.css line 142\"\n106: }\n107: ```\n108: \n109: This schema — `user-query`, `title`, `thought`, `action{code,output}`, `answer`, `side-effect` — turned out to be the **minimal complete vocabulary** for any agent that has thoughts, takes actions, and produces answers.\n110: \n111: ### 2.2 Phase 2: `.ailog` Format (June 2026)\n112: \n113: The schema was formalized as `.ailog` — a single-file, vendor-neutral transcript format for AI agent sessions. A detailed analysis identified 85 use cases across personal, team, community, commercial, and educational categories.\n114: \n115: The key insight: **every AI coding agent produces the same conceptual output** (thoughts + actions + answers), but they all store it differently. A shared format would enable:\n116: - Portable session archives\n117: - Cross-tool context hydration\n118: - Searchable AI history\n119: - Reproducible agent traces\n120: \n121: ### 2.3 Phase 3: AgentSON (July 2026)\n122: \n123: `.ailog` evolved into **AgentSON** as the scope expanded from Chrome DevTools to cover all AI coding agents on the system. The name is a play on **JSON** — **Agent + JSON** — \"Yet Another JSON\" but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n124: \n125: **Agent Session Object Notation** — a structured representation of agent session data that can be read, written, and transferred across any tooling.\n126: \n127: **File extension:** `.AgentSON`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## 3. Product Vision\n132: \n133: ### 3.1 What AgentSON Is\n134: \n\n(Showing lines 105-134 of 718. Use offset=135 to continue.)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783217811485
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\README.md\", \"offset\": 270, \"limit\": 40}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n270: │   └── web/index.html     # ✅ Working (drag-and-drop viewer)\n271: ├── training/\n272: │   └── opencode_example_unsloth.jsonl  # Example training data\n273: └── docs/\n274:     └── sops/              # 14 Standard Operating Procedures\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ## Origin\n278: \n279: AgentSON evolved from `.ailog` — a format originally designed for Chrome DevTools AI session export. The schema was discovered in Chrome's Preferences JSON and generalized to cover all AI coding agents.\n280: \n281: The name \"AgentSON\" is a play on JSON — **Agent + JSON** — \"Yet Another JSON\" but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n282: \n283: ### What Changed from .ailog\n284: \n285: | Aspect | .ailog | AgentSON |\n286: |--------|--------|----------|\n287: | Scope | Chrome DevTools only | All AI coding agents |\n288: | Schema | Undocumented | JSON Schema v1 |\n289: | File extension | `.ailog` | `.AgentSON` |\n290: | Name meaning | AI Log | Agent + JSON |\n291: \n292: See [PRD.md](PRD.md) for the full product requirements document.\n293: \n294: ## License\n295: \n296: MIT\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: *\"Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs or what containers.dev did for dev environments.\"*\n\n(End of file - total 300 lines)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783217811811
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\README.md\", \"offset\": 40, \"limit\": 20}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n40: \n41: ## File Extension\n42: \n43: AgentSON files use the `.AgentSON` extension:\n44: \n45: ```\n46: my-session.AgentSON\n47: ```\n48: \n49: This makes them:\n50: - **Immediately identifiable** — not `.json` (too generic), not `.ailog` (old name)\n51: - **Grep-friendly** — `grep -r \"nightscout\" *.AgentSON`\n52: - **Tool-associated** — can be associated with the AgentSON CLI or viewer\n53: - **Windows-friendly** — `.agentson` (lowercase) also works on Windows\n54: \n55: ## Quick Start\n56: \n57: ```bash\n58: # Install\n59: pip install -e .\n\n(Showing lines 40-59 of 300. Use offset=60 to continue.)\n</content>",
