      "text": "Here is my complete findings report.\n\n---\n\n## Search Results: \".ailog\" / \"ailog\" in C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\n\n### 1. Folders Named \"ailog\" or Containing \"ailog\"\n\n**No dedicated \"ailog\" folder exists.** The path `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\ailog\\` does not exist (file not found).\n\n### 2. Files with \"ailog\" in the Filename\n\n**No files** with \"ailog\" in the filename exist anywhere under `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents`. No `.ailog` files exist on disk.\n\n### 3. Git Repos with \"ailog\" in the Name\n\nThe repository at `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\` is a git repo that has extensive history referencing `.ailog`. It is the successor project to `.ailog`. The branch name was previously `agentson-landing` (visible in reflog). Key git evidence:\n\n| Commit Hash | Message |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `62b0e41` | \"Add AgentSON landing page (rebranded from .ailog copy)\" |\n| `4f65fcb` | \"Restore original .ailog layout with amber tokens\" |\n\nThe reflog shows this branch was originally `agentson-landing`, then renamed to `master`. The history was squashed into a clean commit (`d5d0e85`) so these earlier commits are orphaned but still reachable via reflog.\n\n### 4. Files Containing References to \".ailog\" (Content Matches)\n\n**15 matches across 6 files:**\n\n| # | Full Path | Type of Reference |\n|---|-----------|-------------------|\n| 1 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\PRD.md` | Phase 2 section: \"The schema was formalized as `.ailog`\" and \"`.ailog` evolved into **AgentSON**\" |\n| 2 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md` | File extension comparison table, origin section, \"not `.ailog` (old name)\" |\n| 3 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\sops\\CHROME-DEVTOOLS-AI-MECHANISM.md` | \"The .ailog Schema (Original)\" section with the original Chrome DevTools JSON schema |\n| 4 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\.git\\logs\\refs\\heads\\master` | Git commit log: \"Restore original .ailog layout with amber tokens\" |\n| 5 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\.git\\logs\\HEAD` | Git reflog: \"Add AgentSON landing page (rebranded from .ailog copy)\" and \"Restore original .ailog layout with amber tokens\" |\n| 6 | `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\find_agentson_minimax.py` | SQL query searching for `%.ailog%` and `%ailog%` in MiniMax SQLite data |\n\n### 5. HTML Landing Pages\n\nThere is **no standalone `.ailog` HTML landing page on disk.** However, git commit `62b0e41` is titled \"Add AgentSON landing page (rebranded from .ailog copy)\" -- this confirms the current AgentSON landing pages were rebranded from an original `.ailog` copy. The landing pages that exist now are:\n\n**Primary landing pages (rebranded from .ailog):**\n\n1. **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\index.html`** -- Main project root landing page (441 lines, full content shown above). Title: \"AgentSON -- Agent + JSON\". This is the current canonical landing page.\n\n2. **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\index.html`** -- GitHub Pages landing page (441 lines, identical content to the root index.html). This is what gets served at the GitHub Pages URL.\n\n3. **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\dev\\index.html`** -- Dev docs variant of the landing page (435 lines). Nearly identical but with emoji prefixes in the card headings and a nav bar.\n\n**Other HTML files in the repo (not landing pages per se):**\n\n4. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\viewers\\web\\index.html` -- Standalone web viewer (older version, blue theme)\n5. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\viewer\\index.html` -- Enhanced web viewer (amber theme, 363 lines, with search/sort/copy/download features)\n6. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\pwa\\index.html` -- PWA viewer (413 lines, blue theme)\n7. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\sops\\index.html` -- SOPs index page\n8. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\404.html` -- 404 error page\n\n### 6. The Original .ailog Schema (from git/docs)\n\nThe original `.ailog` schema is documented in `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\sops\\CHROME-DEVTOOLS-AI-MECHANISM.md` (lines 423-448):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"user-query\": \"Why is this element not visible?\",\n  \"title\": \"Debugging visibility issue\",\n  \"thought\": \"The element might have display:none or visibility:hidden\",\n  \"action\": {\n    \"code\": \"getComputedStyle(element).display\",\n    \"output\": \"none\"\n  },\n  \"answer\": \"The element has display: none set in the CSS\",\n  \"side-effect\": {\n    \"action\": \"file_write\",\n    \"path\": \"styles.css\"\n  },\n  \"context\": {\n    \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n    \"element\": \"div#main\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Full Content of the Primary Landing Page\n\nThe main landing page was provided in full above: `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\index.html` (441 lines). This is the rebranded version of the original `.ailog` landing page. The git commit message explicitly states: \"Add AgentSON landing page (rebranded from .ailog copy)\".\n\n### Summary\n\n- **No `.ailog` files or `ailog` folders exist on disk** -- the directory `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\ailog\\` does not exist.\n- **`.ailog` was the predecessor format** to `.AgentSON`, originating from Chrome DevTools AI session export.\n- **All references to `.ailog` are textual** -- in documentation (PRD.md, README.md, CHROME-DEVTOOLS-AI-MECHANISM.md), a Python script (find_agentson_minimax.py), and git history.\n- **The current HTML landing pages are rebranded copies** of the original `.ailog` landing page, as confirmed by git commit `62b0e41`.\n- The only git repo with `.ailog` history is **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\`**.",
